## Edge cases

- **Pre-revenue** — skip MoM growth scenarios, focus on burn + one-time expense scenarios. Raise-by date is computed from burn only.
- **Revenue larger than burn (profitable)** — invert the model. Surface "months until X reserve target" instead of cash-out date. Default reserve target: 12 months of burn.
- **Lumpy revenue** (enterprise, annual contracts) — AskUserQuestion: "Stripe shows lumpy revenue. Use trailing 6-month average, or annualized contract value? The choice affects MoM growth rate significantly."
- **One-time inflows (grant, prior round closing)** — flag as one-time, don't include in the recurring revenue trend. Add as a scenario instead.
- **Multi-currency** — AskUserQuestion: "Bank is in {USD}, Stripe charges in {EUR/GBP}. Use today's FX rate or trailing 6-month average?"
- **Outdated bank.csv** — if newest row is >14 days old, refuse to run until refreshed. Show: "Latest bank.csv row is {N} days old. Refresh before modeling — stale data leads to wrong decisions."
- **Scenario combinations** — when user asks for "hire X AND cut Y", model as a single combined scenario named "hire X + cut Y". Don't add scenarios mechanically; combinations are decisions.

